## **Description**
The **Subtract **operator allows to subtract multiple numeric values from a numeric value provided in input.

## **Input**
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**in0**

Number

The numeric value from which you want to subtract the other numeric values

**inâ€¦**

Number

The N-th numeric value that you want to subtract

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**out0**

Number

The result of the subtraction

## **![](data:image/png;base64,)****Settings**
- In the **Inputs **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an input node to the list.

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

> Tip

To rename an input node, click on its name to edit it.

To remove an input node from the list, move your mouse over it and click![](data:image/png;base64,) in the **Action **column; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## **Special cases**
In special cases, the operator behaves as follows:

**Case**

**Behavior**

**NULL input (no input)**

The operator considers a NULL input as ***0***. The system logs a warning event.

**NULL input value**

The operator considers a NULL input value as ***0***. The system logs a warning event.

**NON NUMERIC input value**

The operator considers a non-numeric input as ***0***. The system logs a warning event.
